PII de-identification agent — Cline rules.

De-identify documents in data/: detect personal data, redact it, and score the
privacy/utility tradeoff. The tools in tools/ do all detection, redaction, and
scoring; you pick inputs and read outputs and never decide what counts as PII or
estimate a score yourself.

For every document:
1. python -m tools.deidentify --json > reports/_scan.json   # counts per type:
   EMAIL, SSN, PHONE, PERSON, ACCOUNT
2. Save the redacted field to reports/<doc>.redacted.txt; confirm placeholders
   ([EMAIL], [SSN], [PHONE], [PERSON], [ACCOUNT]).
3. python -m tools.metrics > reports/_metrics.json          # privacy and utility
4. If privacy < 1.0, an identifier leaked — name the type and re-detect; if utility
   is low, redaction was too aggressive — flag the span.
5. Save counts and both scores to reports/<doc>.md.

Never paste an original identifier back into redacted text and never estimate a
metric. Run tests with: python -m pytest -q
